# 📖 Encoding Techniques

## 1️⃣ Ordinal Encoding

Used when categories have a natural order.

### Example

Education Level

```
High School → 0
Bachelor's → 1
Master's → 2
PhD → 3
```

✅ Best for ordered categorical features.

---

## 2️⃣ Label Encoding

Assigns an integer to every category.

Example

```
Apple → 0
Banana → 1
Orange → 2
```

⚠️ Not recommended for nominal data because the model may assume an order.

---

## 3️⃣ One Hot Encoding

Creates a separate binary column for each category.

Example

Color

| Color | Red | Blue | Green |
|-------|----:|-----:|------:|
| Red | 1 | 0 | 0 |
| Blue | 0 | 1 | 0 |
| Green | 0 | 0 | 1 |

✅ Most commonly used encoding technique.

---

## 4️⃣ Dummy Variable Trap

Occurs when all dummy variables are used.

To avoid multicollinearity:

Drop one dummy column.

---

## 5️⃣ Frequency Encoding

Replace each category by its frequency.

Example

```
Delhi -> 320
Mumbai -> 280
Pune -> 150
```

Useful for high-cardinality features.

---

## 6️⃣ Target Encoding

Replace category with target mean.

Example

```
City

Delhi → Average Salary = 9.2 LPA
Mumbai → Average Salary = 8.5 LPA
```

Mostly used in advanced Machine Learning competitions.

